{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017Je6dCbZyDCQXyr89oX2Kh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 3.1: Audit Coordinator & Dimensions\n     2→\n     3→Status: verifying\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→## Story\n     8→\n     9→As an operator,\n    10→I want `codeharness audit` to check all compliance dimensions in one command,\n    11→so that I see full project health instantly.\n    12→\n    13→## Acceptance Criteria\n    14→\n    15→1. **Given** `codeharness audit` is run, **When** it completes, **Then** output shows status for each dimension: observability (static + runtime), testing, documentation, verification, infrastructure -- using UX prefix format (`[OK]`/`[FAIL]`/`[WARN]`). <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→2. **Given** each dimension, **When** checked, **Then** it produces a status (pass/fail/warn) and a metric (% or grade). <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→3. **Given** audit completes, **When** measured, **Then** it runs in <30 seconds for a 100K LOC project. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→4. **Given** `--json` flag, **When** audit runs, **Then** output is structured JSON with all dimension results, each containing `status`, `metric`, and `gaps` arrays. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→5. **Given** gaps found, **When** displayed in human-readable mode, **Then** each gap has a specific description and suggested fix, printed as `[WARN] dimension: description -- fix: remedy`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→6. **Given** `codeharness audit` runs, **When** the observability stack is not available or Semgrep is not installed, **Then** those dimensions report `warn` with a skip reason -- not a hard failure that blocks the entire audit. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→7. **Given** `codeharness audit` runs with no project initialized, **When** the harness state file is missing, **Then** it exits with `[FAIL] Harness not initialized -- run codeharness init first`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→\n    23→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    24→\n    25→- [x] Task 1: Define audit types in `src/modules/audit/types.ts` (AC: #1, #2, #4)\n    26→  - [x] 1.1: Define `DimensionStatus = 'pass' | 'fail' | 'warn'`\n    27→  - [x] 1.2: Define `DimensionResult` interface: `{ name: string; status: DimensionStatus; metric: string; gaps: AuditGap[]; }`\n    28→  - [x] 1.3: Define `AuditGap` interface: `{ dimension: string; description: string; suggestedFix: string; }`\n    29→  - [x] 1.4: Define `AuditResult` interface: `{ dimensions: Record<string, DimensionResult>; overallStatus: DimensionStatus; gapCount: number; durationMs: number; }`\n    30→\n    31→- [x] Task 2: Implement dimension checkers in `src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts` (AC: #1, #2, #5, #6)\n    32→  - [x] 2.1: `checkObservability(projectDir: string): Result<DimensionResult>` -- calls `analyze()` from `observability/index.ts` for static coverage and `validateRuntime()` for runtime coverage. If Semgrep not installed or backend unreachable, return `warn` status with skip reason.\n    33→  - [x] 2.2: `checkTesting(projectDir: string): Result<DimensionResult>` -- calls `checkOnlyCoverage()` or `evaluateCoverage()` from `lib/coverage.ts`. Reports test coverage % as metric.\n    34→  - [x] 2.3: `checkDocumentation(projectDir: string): Result<DimensionResult>` -- calls `scanDocHealth()` from `lib/doc-health.ts`. Reports doc freshness status.\n    35→  - [x] 2.4: `checkVerification(projectDir: string): Result<DimensionResult>` -- calls `parseProof()` from `verify/index.ts` or reads verification state from sprint-state.json. Reports verified story count.\n    36→  - [x] 2.5: `checkInfrastructure(projectDir: string): Result<DimensionResult>` -- checks if Dockerfile exists, basic structural validation (pinned FROM, no :latest). Full Dockerfile validation is Story 4.1; here just check existence and basic rules.\n    37→  - [x] 2.6: Each checker catches its own errors and returns `warn`/`fail` DimensionResult -- never throws (AC #6).\n    38→\n    39→- [x] Task 3: Implement audit coordinator in `src/modules/audit/index.ts` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #6)\n    40→  - [x] 3.1: `runAudit(projectDir: string): Result<AuditResult>` -- calls all 5 dimension checkers, collects results, computes `overallStatus` (fail if any fail, warn if any warn, pass if all pass), counts total gaps.\n    41→  - [x] 3.2: Wrap audit execution with `performance.now()` timing to populate `durationMs` (AC #3).\n    42→  - [x] 3.3: Export `runAudit` from barrel.\n    43→\n    44→- [x] Task 4: Implement report formatter in `src/modules/audit/report.ts` (AC: #4, #5)\n    45→  - [x] 4.1: `formatAuditHuman(result: AuditResult): string[]` -- formats each dimension as `[OK] dimension: metric` or `[FAIL] dimension: metric` with gaps listed below as `  [WARN] description -- fix: remedy`.\n    46→  - [x] 4.2: `formatAuditJson(result: AuditResult): object` -- returns structured JSON matching the AuditResult shape for `--json` output.\n    47→\n    48→- [x] Task 5: Register CLI command in `src/commands/audit.ts` (AC: #1, #4, #7)\n    49→  - [x] 5.1: Create `registerAuditCommand(program: Command)` with `codeharness audit` command.\n    50→  - [x] 5.2: Add `--json` option for machine-readable output.\n    51→  - [x] 5.3: Run preconditions check -- if not initialized, exit with fail message (AC #7).\n    52→  - [x] 5.4: Call `runAudit(process.cwd())`, then format output based on `--json` flag.\n    53→  - [x] 5.5: Register command in `src/cli.ts` (or wherever commands are registered).\n    54→\n    55→- [x] Task 6: Write unit tests (AC: all)\n    56→  - [x] 6.1: Create `src/modules/audit/__tests__/dimensions.test.ts`:\n    57→    - Test each dimension checker returns `DimensionResult` with correct status and metric\n    58→    - Test observability checker returns `warn` when Semgrep not installed\n    59→    - Test observability checker returns `warn` when backend unreachable\n    60→    - Test infrastructure checker returns `fail` when no Dockerfile\n    61→    - Test infrastructure checker returns `warn` for unpinned base image\n    62→  - [x] 6.2: Create `src/modules/audit/__tests__/index.test.ts`:\n    63→    - Test `runAudit` calls all 5 dimensions\n    64→    - Test `overallStatus` = fail when any dimension fails\n    65→    - Test `overallStatus` = warn when any dimension warns (and none fail)\n    66→    - Test `overallStatus` = pass when all pass\n    67→    - Test gapCount aggregation\n    68→    - Test durationMs is populated\n    69→  - [x] 6.3: Create `src/modules/audit/__tests__/report.test.ts`:\n    70→    - Test human format includes `[OK]`/`[FAIL]`/`[WARN]` prefixes\n    71→    - Test human format lists gaps with suggested fixes\n    72→    - Test JSON format matches AuditResult structure\n    73→  - [x] 6.4: Create `src/commands/__tests__/audit.test.ts`:\n    74→    - Test command registration\n    75→    - Test `--json` produces valid JSON\n    76→    - Test exit with fail message when not initialized\n    77→  - [x] 6.5: Mock all I/O: filesystem, subprocess (Semgrep), HTTP (observability backend)\n    78→  - [x] 6.6: Target 100% coverage on new files\n    79→\n    80→- [x] Task 7: Integration verification (AC: all)\n    81→  - [x] 7.1: `npm run build` -- verify tsup compiles new module\n    82→  - [x] 7.2: `npm run test:unit` -- all tests pass, no regressions\n    83→  - [x] 7.3: Verify module boundaries: only barrel `index.ts` exports public API\n    84→  - [x] 7.4: Verify no file exceeds 300 lines (NFR9)\n    85→  - [x] 7.5: Verify audit runs on codeharness itself and produces output\n    86→\n    87→## Dev Notes\n    88→\n    89→### Architecture References\n    90→\n    91→This story implements FR13 (full compliance report), FR14 (per-dimension status + metric), FR21 (structured output), and partially FR17-FR20 (dimension checks). It is Architecture Decision 4: Coordinator Pattern.\n    92→\n    93→The audit module is a coordinator that calls existing modules + the new observability module. It does NOT reimplement any dimension logic -- it delegates to existing functions and standardizes the output.\n    94→\n    95→### Key Implementation Details\n    96→\n    97→**Coordinator pattern (Decision 4):** `runAudit()` calls 5 dimension checkers sequentially. Each checker wraps an existing module function and maps its output to `DimensionResult`. The coordinator collects all results and computes an overall status.\n    98→\n    99→**Dimension checkers call existing code:**\n   100→- Observability: `analyze()` from `src/modules/observability/index.ts` (static) + `validateRuntime()` (runtime)\n   101→- Testing: `checkOnlyCoverage()` from `src/lib/coverage.ts` (reads last coverage report without re-running tests)\n   102→- Documentation: `scanDocHealth()` from `src/lib/doc-health.ts`\n   103→- Verification: read from sprint-state.json or call `parseProof()` from `verify/index.ts`\n   104→- Infrastructure: basic Dockerfile existence + format check (full validation is Story 4.1)\n   105→\n   106→**Graceful degradation (AC #6):** Each dimension checker catches its own errors. If Semgrep is not installed, the observability static check returns `warn` with skip reason. If the observability backend is unreachable, runtime check returns `warn`. If no Dockerfile exists, infrastructure returns `fail` with \"no Dockerfile found -- run codeharness init\". The audit never crashes due to one dimension failing.\n   107→\n   108→**Performance (AC #3, NFR1):** Audit must complete in <30 seconds. Since all dimension checks read cached state or do lightweight scans (no test execution, no Docker builds), this should be achievable. `checkOnlyCoverage` reads the last coverage report. `scanDocHealth` scans file metadata. `analyze` runs Semgrep which typically finishes in <10 seconds. `validateRuntime` checks backend health (3s timeout) and may skip.\n   109→\n   110→**Output format (AC #5, NFR5):** Follow the UX spec prefix format: `[OK]`, `[FAIL]`, `[WARN]`. Use the existing `ok()`, `fail()`, `warn()`, `info()` helpers from `src/lib/output.ts`. For `--json`, use `jsonOutput()`.\n   111→\n   112→**`onboard` alias is NOT this story.** Story 3.3 makes `onboard` an alias for `audit`. This story creates the new `audit` command only.\n   113→\n   114→**`--fix` is NOT this story.** Story 3.2 implements `audit --fix` story generation. This story only does the audit reporting.\n   115→\n   116→### Existing Code to Reuse\n   117→\n   118→- `src/modules/observability/index.ts` -- `analyze()`, `validateRuntime()`, `readCoverageState()` for observability dimension\n   119→- `src/lib/coverage.ts` -- `checkOnlyCoverage()`, `evaluateCoverage()` for testing dimension\n   120→- `src/lib/doc-health.ts` -- `scanDocHealth()` for documentation dimension\n   121→- `src/modules/verify/index.ts` -- `parseProof()` for verification dimension\n   122→- `src/lib/output.ts` -- `ok()`, `fail()`, `warn()`, `info()`, `jsonOutput()` for output formatting\n   123→- `src/types/result.ts` -- `Result<T>`, `ok()`, `fail()`, `isOk()`, `isFail()` for return types\n   124→- `src/commands/onboard.ts` -- reference for command registration pattern and precondition checks (`runPreconditions()` from `src/lib/onboard-checks.ts`)\n   125→- `src/lib/state.ts` -- state file reading for verification status\n   126→\n   127→### What This Story Does NOT Include\n   128→\n   129→- No `--fix` flag or story generation -- that's Story 3.2\n   130→- No `onboard` alias -- that's Story 3.3\n   131→- No full Dockerfile validation against rules -- that's Story 4.1 (here just check existence + basic structural validation)\n   132→- No static analysis rule authoring -- that's Epic 1 (done)\n   133→- No runtime observability during verification -- that's Story 2.1 (done)\n   134→- No hook enforcement -- that's Story 2.2 (done)\n   135→- No OpenSearch backend support -- VictoriaLogs only; OpenSearch is future\n   136→\n   137→### Dependencies\n   138→\n   139→- **Depends on:** Story 1.2 (analyzer module, `analyze()`) -- DONE\n   140→- **Depends on:** Story 1.3 (coverage state tracking, `readCoverageState()`) -- DONE\n   141→- **Depends on:** Story 2.3 (standalone runtime validator, `validateRuntime()`) -- DONE\n   142→- **Depended on by:** Story 3.2 (audit --fix, calls `runAudit()`)\n   143→- **Depended on by:** Story 3.3 (onboard alias, delegates to audit command)\n   144→\n   145→### File Size Constraint\n   146→\n   147→Each new file must be under 300 lines per NFR9.\n   148→- `src/modules/audit/types.ts` -- ~40-50 lines\n   149→- `src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts` -- ~150-200 lines (5 checkers)\n   150→- `src/modules/audit/index.ts` -- ~60-80 lines (coordinator + barrel)\n   151→- `src/modules/audit/report.ts` -- ~80-100 lines (human + JSON formatters)\n   152→- `src/commands/audit.ts` -- ~50-70 lines (command registration)\n   153→\n   154→### Previous Story Intelligence (Story 2.3)\n   155→\n   156→- **`validateRuntime()` returns `RuntimeValidationResult`** whose shape includes `coveragePercent`, `skipped`, `skipReason`, and `entries: ModuleTelemetryEntry[]`. The audit coordinator must handle the `skipped: true` case by mapping to `warn` status.\n   157→- **Barrel imports only.** Import from `../observability/index.js`, never from internal files like `../observability/runtime-validator.js`.\n   158→- **Mock all I/O in tests.** All filesystem, HTTP, and subprocess operations mocked. No real calls.\n   159→- **Atomic write pattern** for any state file updates (read-modify-write with temp+rename).\n   160→- **`checkBackendHealth` has 3-second timeout.** Audit won't hang waiting for an unreachable backend.\n   161→- **`types.ts` is 293 lines.** Near the 300-line NFR9 limit. Do NOT add audit types there -- put them in `src/modules/audit/types.ts`.\n   162→- **Story 2.3 explicitly says:** \"No CLI command in this story -- the audit command will orchestrate calling this.\" That's us. We call `validateRuntime()`.\n   163→\n   164→### Git Intelligence\n   165→\n   166→Recent commits show Epic 0.5 (stream-json live activity display) and Epic 2 (runtime observability) completed. The project uses:\n   167→- Commander for CLI commands\n   168→- `Result<T>` discriminated union for error handling\n   169→- tsup for building\n   170→- Vitest for testing (2656+ tests as of story 2.3)\n   171→- Barrel exports (`index.ts`) for module boundaries\n   172→\n   173→### References\n   174→\n   175→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md#Decision 4] -- Audit coordinator pattern\n   176→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md#Decision 6] -- Module structure (audit/ directory)\n   177→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-operational-excellence.md#Story 3.1] -- Acceptance criteria\n   178→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-operational-excellence.md#Audit Command] -- FR13, FR14, FR17-FR21\n   179→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-specification.md#Output Patterns] -- Status prefix format\n   180→- [Source: src/modules/observability/index.ts] -- analyze(), validateRuntime() exports\n   181→- [Source: src/lib/coverage.ts] -- checkOnlyCoverage(), evaluateCoverage()\n   182→- [Source: src/lib/doc-health.ts] -- scanDocHealth()\n   183→- [Source: src/modules/verify/index.ts] -- parseProof()\n   184→- [Source: src/commands/onboard.ts] -- Command registration pattern reference\n   185→- [Source: src/lib/onboard-checks.ts] -- runPreconditions() for init check\n   186→\n   187→### Project Structure Notes\n   188→\n   189→- New module: `src/modules/audit/` with `types.ts`, `dimensions.ts`, `index.ts`, `report.ts`, `__tests__/`\n   190→- New command: `src/commands/audit.ts`\n   191→- No patches created in this story (workflow patches are Epic 5)\n   192→- Module follows existing conventions: barrel exports, Result<T> returns, <300 line files\n   193→\n   194→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   195→## Verification Requirements\n   196→\n   197→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions.proof.md`)\n   198→- [x] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   199→- [x] Test coverage meets target (100% of all new code in src/)\n   200→\n   201→## Documentation Requirements\n   202→\n   203→- [x] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (src/modules/audit/AGENTS.md)\n   204→- [x] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions.md`\n   205→\n   206→## Testing Requirements\n   207→\n   208→- [x] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   209→- [x] All I/O mocked (filesystem, subprocess, HTTP)\n   210→- [x] Coverage target: 100%\n   211→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   212→\n   213→## Dev Agent Record\n   214→\n   215→### Agent Model Used\n   216→\n   217→Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n   218→\n   219→### Debug Log References\n   220→\n   221→### Completion Notes List\n   222→\n   223→- Implemented audit coordinator module with 5 dimension checkers (observability, testing, documentation, verification, infrastructure)\n   224→- Each dimension checker wraps an existing module function and maps output to DimensionResult\n   225→- Coordinator uses Promise.all for parallel execution of dimension checkers with performance.now() timing\n   226→- Human output uses [OK]/[FAIL]/[WARN] prefix format per UX spec; --json returns structured AuditResult\n   227→- Graceful degradation: each checker catches its own errors, returns warn/fail instead of crashing\n   228→- CLI command registered as `codeharness audit` with --json option and precondition check for initialization\n   229→- 47 new tests across 4 test files, all I/O mocked (filesystem, subprocess, HTTP)\n   230→- Build passes, 2769 total tests pass (0 regressions), all files under 300-line NFR9 limit\n   231→- Updated cli.test.ts command count from 22 to 23 to include new audit command\n   232→- dimensions.ts initially 428 lines; refactored to 197 lines using helper functions to stay under NFR9\n   233→\n   234→### Change Log\n   235→\n   236→- 2026-03-20: Story 3.1 implementation complete — audit coordinator, dimensions, report formatter, CLI command, tests\n   237→- 2026-03-20: Senior Developer Review (AI) — adversarial review found 10 issues (2 HIGH, 5 MEDIUM, 3 LOW). Fixed all HIGH and MEDIUM: added 10 new tests covering error paths, catch branches, runtime low-coverage, readdirSafe failure, runAudit failure CLI paths, dimension checker failure handling. Simplified formatAuditJson. 57 tests total, 100% line coverage on all files, 96.71% overall, all files above 80% floor. 2779 total tests, 0 regressions.\n   238→\n   239→### File List\n   240→\n   241→- src/modules/audit/types.ts (new, 43 lines)\n   242→- src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts (new, 197 lines)\n   243→- src/modules/audit/index.ts (new, 85 lines)\n   244→- src/modules/audit/report.ts (new, 62 lines)\n   245→- src/modules/audit/AGENTS.md (new)\n   246→- src/commands/audit.ts (new, 66 lines)\n   247→- src/index.ts (modified — added registerAuditCommand import and registration)\n   248→- src/__tests__/cli.test.ts (modified — updated command count from 22 to 23, added 'audit' to expected list)\n   249→- src/modules/audit/__tests__/dimensions.test.ts (new, 24 tests)\n   250→- src/modules/audit/__tests__/index.test.ts (new, 7 tests)\n   251→- src/modules/audit/__tests__/report.test.ts (new, 10 tests)\n   252→- src/commands/__tests__/audit.test.ts (new, 6 tests)\n   253→- docs/exec-plans/active/3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions.md (new)\n   254→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01GUR1dsNVzUTLzShG1rFUcD","session_id":"0deb1693-f450-4ee3-ba9f-130c7ba0aec5","uuid":"6c85ec1e-c96f-4471-8f00-7bf04e78d020","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:11:58.535Z"}
