{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015ZVcF7yz9jpcoUEHnLEhKA","type":"tool_result","content":"34-\n35-1. **Observability enforcement** — three layers of measurement. Static analysis scans source for log coverage. Runtime validation confirms telemetry flows during test runs. An observability coverage metric (% of code paths with telemetry) gives a trackable number, enforced like test coverage.\n36-\n37:2. **`codeharness audit`** — comprehensive compliance check replacing `onboard`. Runs anytime, checks everything (observability, testing, docs, verification, infrastructure), generates fix stories for gaps. `onboard` becomes an alias.\n38-\n39-3. **Infrastructure development guidelines** — verification Dockerfile is a project artifact with formalized rules, validated by audit. The agent maintains it during development. Eliminates the recurring \"container doesn't have the binary\" class of bugs.\n40-\n--\n57-\n58-- **Observability has a number.** Every project gets an observability coverage % from `codeharness audit`.\n59-- **Audit is instant.** `codeharness audit` returns full compliance report in <30 seconds.\n60:- **Gaps become stories.** `codeharness audit --fix` generates implementable stories for every gap.\n61-- **Infrastructure stays correct.** Zero \"container missing binary\" failures when Dockerfile is a maintained project artifact.\n62-\n63-### Technical Success\n--\n73-| Observability coverage metric exists | Yes — every audit produces a % |\n74-| Audit covers all dimensions | Observability + testing + docs + verification + infra |\n75-| Audit runtime | <30 seconds |\n76:| Audit --fix generates stories | Stories with ACs for each gap |\n77-| Infrastructure audit catches Dockerfile drift | Before verification fails |\n78-| Static analysis flags per code review | Missing logs flagged during review |\n79-\n--\n122-\n123-- **FR13:** Operator can run `codeharness audit` to get a full compliance report covering: observability, testing, documentation, verification, infrastructure.\n124-- **FR14:** Each audit dimension produces a status (pass/fail/warn) and a metric (% or grade).\n125:- **FR15:** Operator can run `codeharness audit --fix` to generate epics/stories for all gaps found.\n126-- **FR16:** `onboard` command becomes an alias for `audit` — same functionality, backward compatible.\n127-- **FR17:** Audit checks verification Dockerfile exists, builds successfully, and contains required tools.\n128-- **FR18:** Audit checks Docker observability stack health (shared or remote).\n--\n150-- **NFR3:** Runtime validation works with both VictoriaMetrics and OpenSearch backends.\n151-- **NFR4:** Observability coverage metric is stored in state file alongside test coverage.\n152-- **NFR5:** Audit output follows the UX spec format (structured sections, status prefixes, actionable remedies).\n153:- **NFR6:** Generated stories from `audit --fix` follow the BMAD story format with Given/When/Then ACs.\n154-- **NFR7:** Infrastructure guidelines are stored as markdown in `patches/infra/` — editable without rebuilding.\n155-- **NFR8:** All new code has 100% test coverage.\n156-- **NFR9:** No source file exceeds 300 lines."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01GUR1dsNVzUTLzShG1rFUcD","session_id":"0deb1693-f450-4ee3-ba9f-130c7ba0aec5","uuid":"553b62dd-5072-43fb-9232-100b5bc62ac6","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:12:43.636Z"}
