{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019zh8V9MYcBfbxC3XqzF7cZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-20 (Session 11)\n     2→\n     3→### 3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions — create-story (2026-03-20T08:39Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **No integration-required ACs:** All 7 ACs are cli-verifiable. Runtime observability dimension internally depends on backend, but AC tests graceful degradation path.\n     6→- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually in harness-run.\n     7→- **Risk: Infrastructure dimension underspecified.** Story 4.1 defines full Dockerfile validation, but this story needs a placeholder for infra dimension. Scoped to \"check Dockerfile existence + basic structural checks.\"\n     8→- **No UX spec for `codeharness audit` specifically.** Derived output format from existing UX prefix patterns (`[OK]`/`[FAIL]`/`[WARN]`).\n     9→\n    10→### 3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions — dev-story (2026-03-20T08:49Z)\n    11→\n    12→- **dimensions.ts exceeded NFR9 (300-line limit)** at 428 lines initially. Compacted to 197 lines — less readable but within constraint.\n    13→- **CLI command test needed exitOverride() pattern** — Commander throws process.exit on unknown commands.\n    14→- **Transient test flake** — 2 failing test files (5 tests) passed on immediate re-run. Not related to this story.\n    15→- **Task 7.5 not verified via actual CLI invocation** — tests cover the path but no real `codeharness audit` run against initialized project.\n    16→- **Coverage not measured per-file** — tests cover all branches structurally but no coverage report generated for new files specifically.\n    17→\n    18→### 3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions — code-review (2026-03-20T08:56Z)\n    19→\n    20→- **HIGH: audit.ts had zero test coverage for runAudit failure path** (both JSON and human output branches) — FIXED, added 2 tests\n    21→- **MEDIUM: 5 uncovered branches** in dimensions.ts and coordinator — all fixed with new tests\n    22→- **MEDIUM: formatAuditJson did pointless property copy** — simplified to direct return\n    23→- **LOW (not fixed): report.ts dead-code fallback `?? '[WARN]'`** — impossible to reach with typed DimensionStatus\n    24→- **LOW (not fixed): readdirSafe uses `as string[]` cast** — fragile if someone adds withFileTypes option\n    25→- **Architecture: checkVerification hardcodes sprint-status.yaml path** — should be configurable but not blocking\n    26→- **Coverage: 96.71% overall, all 116 files above 80% floor, 2779 tests pass**\n    27→\n    28→### 3-2-audit-fix-story-generation — create-story (2026-03-20T09:14Z)\n    29→\n    30→- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually in harness-run.\n    31→- **Expanded ACs from 3 to 10:** Original epic definition had only 3 sparse ACs. Agent expanded to cover edge cases, JSON output, idempotency, atomic writes, and precondition checks.\n    32→- **Risk: Story key collision.** The `audit-fix-{dimension}-{index}` key scheme uses sequential index. If gaps change between runs, same index could map to different gaps. Content-based hash would be more robust.\n    33→- **Risk: sprint-state.json vs sprint-status.yaml divergence.** Epic says stories go to sprint-state.json, but sprint planning also uses sprint-status.yaml. Generated stories won't appear in sprint-status.yaml unless manually synced.\n    34→\n    35→### 3-2-audit-fix-story-generation — dev-story (2026-03-20T09:19Z)\n    36→\n    37→- **Test file exceeds NFR9:** `fix-generator.test.ts` is 426 lines (estimated 200-250). Thorough AC coverage with mocking requires more code. Test files generally exempt from NFR9.\n    38→- **Type gymnastics in audit.ts:** Uses `ReturnType<typeof generateFixStories>` pattern to avoid importing internal Result type. Works but not cleanest.\n    39→- **No end-to-end verification:** Task 7.5 requires `codeharness audit --fix` against a real initialized project — only unit tests cover the paths. E2E test deferred to review.\n    40→- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually in harness-run.\n    41→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0deb1693-f450-4ee3-ba9f-130c7ba0aec5","uuid":"0613b168-228a-4bb1-b01a-2097907735a3","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:25:35.271Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-20 (Session 11)\n\n### 3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions — create-story (2026-03-20T08:39Z)\n\n- **No integration-required ACs:** All 7 ACs are cli-verifiable. Runtime observability dimension internally depends on backend, but AC tests graceful degradation path.\n- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually in harness-run.\n- **Risk: Infrastructure dimension underspecified.** Story 4.1 defines full Dockerfile validation, but this story needs a placeholder for infra dimension. Scoped to \"check Dockerfile existence + basic structural checks.\"\n- **No UX spec for `codeharness audit` specifically.** Derived output format from existing UX prefix patterns (`[OK]`/`[FAIL]`/`[WARN]`).\n\n### 3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions — dev-story (2026-03-20T08:49Z)\n\n- **dimensions.ts exceeded NFR9 (300-line limit)** at 428 lines initially. Compacted to 197 lines — less readable but within constraint.\n- **CLI command test needed exitOverride() pattern** — Commander throws process.exit on unknown commands.\n- **Transient test flake** — 2 failing test files (5 tests) passed on immediate re-run. Not related to this story.\n- **Task 7.5 not verified via actual CLI invocation** — tests cover the path but no real `codeharness audit` run against initialized project.\n- **Coverage not measured per-file** — tests cover all branches structurally but no coverage report generated for new files specifically.\n\n### 3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions — code-review (2026-03-20T08:56Z)\n\n- **HIGH: audit.ts had zero test coverage for runAudit failure path** (both JSON and human output branches) — FIXED, added 2 tests\n- **MEDIUM: 5 uncovered branches** in dimensions.ts and coordinator — all fixed with new tests\n- **MEDIUM: formatAuditJson did pointless property copy** — simplified to direct return\n- **LOW (not fixed): report.ts dead-code fallback `?? '[WARN]'`** — impossible to reach with typed DimensionStatus\n- **LOW (not fixed): readdirSafe uses `as string[]` cast** — fragile if someone adds withFileTypes option\n- **Architecture: checkVerification hardcodes sprint-status.yaml path** — should be configurable but not blocking\n- **Coverage: 96.71% overall, all 116 files above 80% floor, 2779 tests pass**\n\n### 3-2-audit-fix-story-generation — create-story (2026-03-20T09:14Z)\n\n- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually in harness-run.\n- **Expanded ACs from 3 to 10:** Original epic definition had only 3 sparse ACs. Agent expanded to cover edge cases, JSON output, idempotency, atomic writes, and precondition checks.\n- **Risk: Story key collision.** The `audit-fix-{dimension}-{index}` key scheme uses sequential index. If gaps change between runs, same index could map to different gaps. Content-based hash would be more robust.\n- **Risk: sprint-state.json vs sprint-status.yaml divergence.** Epic says stories go to sprint-state.json, but sprint planning also uses sprint-status.yaml. Generated stories won't appear in sprint-status.yaml unless manually synced.\n\n### 3-2-audit-fix-story-generation — dev-story (2026-03-20T09:19Z)\n\n- **Test file exceeds NFR9:** `fix-generator.test.ts` is 426 lines (estimated 200-250). Thorough AC coverage with mocking requires more code. Test files generally exempt from NFR9.\n- **Type gymnastics in audit.ts:** Uses `ReturnType<typeof generateFixStories>` pattern to avoid importing internal Result type. Works but not cleanest.\n- **No end-to-end verification:** Task 7.5 requires `codeharness audit --fix` against a real initialized project — only unit tests cover the paths. E2E test deferred to review.\n- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually in harness-run.\n","numLines":41,"startLine":1,"totalLines":41}}}
