{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0198sJsz42JRrUfR2eY6zXA1","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0deb1693-f450-4ee3-ba9f-130c7ba0aec5","uuid":"7996059d-ad9e-4984-a248-074f101c36ac","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:25:53.336Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"- **No end-to-end verification:** Task 7.5 requires `codeharness audit --fix` against a real initialized project — only unit tests cover the paths. E2E test deferred to review.\n- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually in harness-run.","newString":"- **No end-to-end verification:** Task 7.5 requires `codeharness audit --fix` against a real initialized project — only unit tests cover the paths. E2E test deferred to review.\n- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually in harness-run.\n\n### 3-2-audit-fix-story-generation — code-review (2026-03-20T09:24Z)\n\n- **HIGH: Error path in fix-generator.ts catch block untested (lines 117-120)** — FIXED with 2 new tests.\n- **MEDIUM: JSON output silently swallowed errors** from generateFixStories() and addFixStoriesToState() in --fix --json mode — FIXED with fixError/fixStateError fields.\n- **MEDIUM: Complex type annotation in audit.ts** — replaced ugly ReturnType inference with clean Result<FixGenerationResult> import.\n- **HIGH: AGENTS.md stale** — missing fix-types.ts and fix-generator.ts entries — FIXED.\n- **LOW (not fixed): fix-types.ts shows 0% coverage** — types-only file, cosmetic artifact.\n- **LOW (not fixed): double-cast in audit.ts line 92** — formatAuditJson return type needs better upstream definition.\n- **Architecture: Story key positional dependency** — index-based scheme shifts when gaps change. Acceptable for current scope.\n- **Coverage: 96.72% overall, all 118 files above 80% floor, 2812 tests pass**","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-20 (Session 11)\n\n### 3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions — create-story (2026-03-20T08:39Z)\n\n- **No integration-required ACs:** All 7 ACs are cli-verifiable. Runtime observability dimension internally depends on backend, but AC tests graceful degradation path.\n- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually in harness-run.\n- **Risk: Infrastructure dimension underspecified.** Story 4.1 defines full Dockerfile validation, but this story needs a placeholder for infra dimension. Scoped to \"check Dockerfile existence + basic structural checks.\"\n- **No UX spec for `codeharness audit` specifically.** Derived output format from existing UX prefix patterns (`[OK]`/`[FAIL]`/`[WARN]`).\n\n### 3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions — dev-story (2026-03-20T08:49Z)\n\n- **dimensions.ts exceeded NFR9 (300-line limit)** at 428 lines initially. Compacted to 197 lines — less readable but within constraint.\n- **CLI command test needed exitOverride() pattern** — Commander throws process.exit on unknown commands.\n- **Transient test flake** — 2 failing test files (5 tests) passed on immediate re-run. Not related to this story.\n- **Task 7.5 not verified via actual CLI invocation** — tests cover the path but no real `codeharness audit` run against initialized project.\n- **Coverage not measured per-file** — tests cover all branches structurally but no coverage report generated for new files specifically.\n\n### 3-1-audit-coordinator-dimensions — code-review (2026-03-20T08:56Z)\n\n- **HIGH: audit.ts had zero test coverage for runAudit failure path** (both JSON and human output branches) — FIXED, added 2 tests\n- **MEDIUM: 5 uncovered branches** in dimensions.ts and coordinator — all fixed with new tests\n- **MEDIUM: formatAuditJson did pointless property copy** — simplified to direct return\n- **LOW (not fixed): report.ts dead-code fallback `?? '[WARN]'`** — impossible to reach with typed DimensionStatus\n- **LOW (not fixed): readdirSafe uses `as string[]` cast** — fragile if someone adds withFileTypes option\n- **Architecture: checkVerification hardcodes sprint-status.yaml path** — should be configurable but not blocking\n- **Coverage: 96.71% overall, all 116 files above 80% floor, 2779 tests pass**\n\n### 3-2-audit-fix-story-generation — create-story (2026-03-20T09:14Z)\n\n- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually in harness-run.\n- **Expanded ACs from 3 to 10:** Original epic definition had only 3 sparse ACs. Agent expanded to cover edge cases, JSON output, idempotency, atomic writes, and precondition checks.\n- **Risk: Story key collision.** The `audit-fix-{dimension}-{index}` key scheme uses sequential index. If gaps change between runs, same index could map to different gaps. Content-based hash would be more robust.\n- **Risk: sprint-state.json vs sprint-status.yaml divergence.** Epic says stories go to sprint-state.json, but sprint planning also uses sprint-status.yaml. Generated stories won't appear in sprint-status.yaml unless manually synced.\n\n### 3-2-audit-fix-story-generation — dev-story (2026-03-20T09:19Z)\n\n- **Test file exceeds NFR9:** `fix-generator.test.ts` is 426 lines (estimated 200-250). Thorough AC coverage with mocking requires more code. Test files generally exempt from NFR9.\n- **Type gymnastics in audit.ts:** Uses `ReturnType<typeof generateFixStories>` pattern to avoid importing internal Result type. Works but not cleanest.\n- **No end-to-end verification:** Task 7.5 requires `codeharness audit --fix` against a real initialized project — only unit tests cover the paths. E2E test deferred to review.\n- **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually in harness-run.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":38,"oldLines":3,"newStart":38,"newLines":14,"lines":[" - **Type gymnastics in audit.ts:** Uses `ReturnType<typeof generateFixStories>` pattern to avoid importing internal Result type. Works but not cleanest."," - **No end-to-end verification:** Task 7.5 requires `codeharness audit --fix` against a real initialized project — only unit tests cover the paths. E2E test deferred to review."," - **sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually in harness-run.","+","+### 3-2-audit-fix-story-generation — code-review (2026-03-20T09:24Z)","+","+- **HIGH: Error path in fix-generator.ts catch block untested (lines 117-120)** — FIXED with 2 new tests.","+- **MEDIUM: JSON output silently swallowed errors** from generateFixStories() and addFixStoriesToState() in --fix --json mode — FIXED with fixError/fixStateError fields.","+- **MEDIUM: Complex type annotation in audit.ts** — replaced ugly ReturnType inference with clean Result<FixGenerationResult> import.","+- **HIGH: AGENTS.md stale** — missing fix-types.ts and fix-generator.ts entries — FIXED.","+- **LOW (not fixed): fix-types.ts shows 0% coverage** — types-only file, cosmetic artifact.","+- **LOW (not fixed): double-cast in audit.ts line 92** — formatAuditJson return type needs better upstream definition.","+- **Architecture: Story key positional dependency** — index-based scheme shifts when gaps change. Acceptable for current scope.","+- **Coverage: 96.72% overall, all 118 files above 80% floor, 2812 tests pass**"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
